<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>Join your Inghams Rep and explore this picturesque area with our 2 day (pre-bookable) cycling programme, starting from the <a data-udi="umb://document/fc538169ce3e4286bfcda7577f595075" href="/{localLink:umb://document/fc538169ce3e4286bfcda7577f595075}" title="Sporthotel Xander (Leutasch)">Hotel Xander</a>. The Leutasch valley is ideal for exploring by bike and our guests rave about being able to enjoy the fresh air and scenery without having to worry about looking at a map! During our rides we take in woodland paths, meadows, rivers and gorges, with plenty of refreshment stops along the way at mountain alms or view points. We always ensure the pace is suitable and relaxed enough for the whole group to enjoy. E-bikes are also available to hire.</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>DAY 1 (Sunday afternoon) | Easy Ride | 3½ hrs (approx) | (20km) </strong></p>
<p><strong>Introduction to the Leutasch Valley &amp; The Geisterklamm Gorge</strong> A lovely gentle trail and a great orientation tour along marked cycle routes and quiet roads through Weidach village and along the river to the Geisterklamm Gorge. There is time to stop for a drink at the café at the entrance or to walk/bike into the gorge itself, before heading back along the river to the hotel.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>DAY 2 (Monday) | Easy/Moderate Ride | 4 hrs (approx) | (20km) </strong></p>
<p><strong>Leutasch to Gaistalalm</strong> A very popular ride with wonderful views and lots of perfect photo opportunities! We start on the flat wide cycle path from Kirchplatzl to Klamm before reaching Salzbach and the narrow mountain path along the Gaistal with magnificent views. The track then heads downhill through pastures to reach the Gaistalalm for a well deserved lunch stop, before returning.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>NB. Bike rides may vary from those published, depending on the group. Places are limited so please pre-book to reserve your place.</strong> Child bikes and child seats are available</p>
</div>
</div>]]></bodyText>
